    en: "A New York tenant whose landlord will not make necessary repairs has three main remedies under the warranty of habitability (Real Property Law 235-b). The tenant can withhold rent, pay for the repair and deduct the cost from future rent, or file an HP action in Housing Court for a court-ordered repair. All three are tools — each with its own risks. Documentation matters in every route. Retaliatory eviction after a tenant asserts warranty rights is barred under RPL 223-b for a year. Self-help without proper documentation can end in eviction, so the safer route for serious cases is usually an HP action."
